President Obama announced his intent to nominate four individuals for key administration posts. Gordon Heddell is nominated for Inspector General of the Department of Defense, Ellen Murray for Assistant Secretary for Resources and Technology at the Department of Health and Human Services, Polly Trottenberg for Assistant Secretary for Transportation Policy at the Department of Transportation, and James J. Markowsky for Assistant Secretary for Fossil Energy at the Department of Energy. Each nominee brings extensive expertise in their respective fields and will be joining the administration during a time of great challenges. President Obama expressed gratitude for their decision to serve and stated that their experience and knowledge will be important in moving America forward towards prosperity and security.